cs.MA, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the coordination of multiple agents, which is a core topic in multi-agent systems (MAS) research. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category. The paper also presents a formalism for describing networking constraint relationships among distributed agents, which falls under the scope of formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper also involves conflict resolution planning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a systematic approach for designing local coordination modules, which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
